column2: Secret Weapons are the result of desperation or the industrious testing of speculative novelties. Sometimes they became decisive instruments of victory and sometimes black holes of resource waste. To start researching a technology in this field, you must already have mastered every technology in an ordinary field. Secret weapons might change the war and might even be the turning point you were looking for. \n Espionage or spying involves an individual obtaining information that is considered secret or confidential without the permission of the holder of the information. Espionage is inherently clandestine, lest the legitimate holder of the information change plans or take other countermeasures once it is known that the information is in unauthorized hands.

column2: These land doctrines were introduced sometimes by directives based on theoretical knowledge and sometimes by a trial and error process. They cover the tactical, organizational and strategic aspects of land combat. There are alternatives  representing different cultural outlooks but also need. A focus on Mobility allows a choice between the blitzkrieg used by the German Wehrmacht and the mass-combat assaults used by the Red Army. A focus on Firepower allows a choice between the offensive fire and movement favored by the US Army and a more defensive doctrine based upon WWI fighting. The latter provides three different versions of firepower doctrine used by the British, the French and the Japanese.

column2: These air doctrines were introduced sometimes by directives based on theoretical knowledge and sometimes by trial and error process. They all cover the tactical, organizational and strategic aspects of air combat. There are modular branches representing different areas of the air war. The Battlefield Destruction is efficient close air support, Operational Destruction is efficient tactical bombing capability and Strategic Destruction is efficient strategic bombing capability. The first two doctrines also provide Offensive Fighter capability while the latter two give Defensive Fighter capability.

column2: These naval doctrines were introduced sometimes by directives based on theoretical knowledge and sometimes by a trial and error process. They cover the tactical, organizational and strategic aspects of naval combat. There are three main choices of doctrine.  Base Strike doctrine results in an offensive navy with excellent carrier capability. Fleet-in-Being doctrine gives the ability to protect and defend sea lanes, and results in a strong surface-combat navy. Sea lane Interdiction doctrine gives an excellent ability to destroy enemy convoys using submarines and surface-combat commerce raiders.
